      "type": "user",
      "content": "How do I configure TLS certificates for the proxy service?"
    },
    {
      "id": "msg-002",
      "timestamp": "2026-01-15T10:00:15.000Z",
      "type": "gemini",
      "content": "",
      "toolCalls": [
        {
          "id": "tc-001",
          "name": "read_file",
          "args": { "file_path": "/etc/proxy/tls.conf" },
          "result": [{ "functionResponse": { "response": { "output": "cert_path = /etc/certs/proxy.pem" } } }],
          "status": "success",
          "timestamp": "2026-01-15T10:00:15.000Z"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "msg-003",
      "timestamp": "2026-01-15T10:00:30.000Z",
      "type": "gemini",
      "content": "To configure TLS certificates for the proxy service, edit `/etc/proxy/tls.conf` and set the `cert_path` directive to point to your PEM certificate file."
    },
    {
      "id": "msg-004",
      "timestamp": "2026-01-15T10:02:00.000Z",
      "type": "user",
      "content": "What about mutual TLS?"
    },
    {
      "id": "msg-005",
      "timestamp": "2026-01-15T10:02:20.000Z",
      "type": "gemini",
      "content": "For mutual TLS, add `client_ca_path` and set `require_client_cert = true` in the same configuration file."
    },
    {
      "id": "msg-006",
      "timestamp": "2026-01-15T10:03:00.000Z",
